result.execSummary:
Timothy A. Swan was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Timothy A. Swan was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:13 pm  
Defendant Timothy A. Swan in court with attorney Liesl E Nelson.  Defendant Timothy A. Swan in custody.  Sean Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def is willing to waive his extradition back to Minnesota.  Court reads the def his right to counsel and the process of the Governor's warrant for extradition.  Def understands his rights.  He is willing to give up those rights.  Court approves the waiver.   The def signs the waiver.  Court signs the waiver of extradition back to Minnesota.
If Defendant is released he must report to the McCloud County, Minnesota Jail within 24-hours of release.

Defendant Timothy A. Swan in Court with Attorney Liesl Nelson.  Defendant Timothy A. Swan in Custody.  DA Sean E Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called at 2:05 p.m.  Atty. Nelson states Defendant is not willing to waive extradition today and requests to be heard on bond.  Atty. Nelson makes bond argument.  DA Froelich objects and notes warrant remaining active.  Crt. questions bond and process, reviews statute.  DA Froelich again objects to bond, Atty. Nelson renews request.  Crt. sets bond.  States Defendant to be held for 30-days pending Governor's Warrant.
